A policeman attached to Zonal Intervention Squad of Zone 2 Police Command yesterday reportedly shot dead a resident of Ifo in Ifo Local Government  Area of Ogun State. The yet – to- be – identified police officer was said to have killed the  young man during a argument. It was gathered that residents in the area protested against the incident by blocking the Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway and burnt tyres. The Police Public Relations Officer, Abimbola Oyeyemi, when contacted, confirmed the incident. Oyeyemi, who noted that he had not been briefed about the incident, said the officer was attached Zonal Intervention Squad. Policeman allegedly kills young man in Ogun One killed as APC, APM supporters clash in Ogun Robbers snatch police officers’ bags, phones in Ogun